    "body": "### Problem\n\n- Documentation\n  - Old spellfile.vim documentation still everywhere\n  - No new documentation\n- Unclear how to set the download URL:\n  - `require('nvim.spellfile').config.url = '...'` is a new pattern never used elsewhere in the codebase to set a user-facing option\n  - No backwards compatibility with `g:spellfile_URL`\n- Error output can be a bit cleaner:\n  ```\n  No spell file found for pr (utf-8). Download? [y/N] yDownloading pr.utf-8.spl …\n  Could not get pr.utf-8.spl (status nil): trying pr.ascii.spl …\n  No spell file available for pr (utf8:curl: (56) The requested URL returned error: 404\n   ascii:curl: (56) The requested URL returned error: 404\n  ) — https://ftp.nluug.nl/pub/vim/runtime/spell/pr.utf-8.spl\n  Warning: Cannot find word list \"pr.utf-8.spl\" or \"pr.ascii.spl\"\n  ```\n- Type annotations use `vim.spellfile` but should use `nvim.spellfile`.\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAt least the documentation should be updated. Maybe we need to wait on https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/34557 for a final decision on how \"core plugins\" are structured (where to place the docs) and interfaced by the end-user (how to configure the plugin).",
